import React, { Component } from "react"; import Title from "../../components/General/Title"; let hasAccount = true; export default class CustomerAccount extends Component { state = { hasAccount: hasAccount, }; render() { return (
{hasAccount ? (
<form style={{ width: 3000 }}> <div class="form-group"> <label for="exampleInputEmail1"> Email address </label> <input type="email" class="form-control" id="exampleInputEmail1" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Enter email" /> </div> <div class="form-group"> <label for="exampleInputPassword1"> Password </label> <input type="password" class="form-control" id="exampleInputPassword1" placeholder="Password" /> </div> <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" > Submit </button> </form> </div> ) : ( <Title name="Create" title="Account" /> )} <div className="row"></div> </div> </div> </React.Fragment> ); } }
